gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: C
task: C2
title: "feat(checkout): runtime CNH-overnight cost parity check vs BE /rates (#1437)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P3
refs:
  - CROP-front#1437
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  At checkout, FE displays CNH-overnight price from a local constant. If BE /rates
  returns a different value (drift or surcharge), the customer sees the wrong price.
  Add a runtime parity check: after fetching /rates, compare overnight rate from BE
  against the FE constant. On mismatch, show the BE value and fire Sentry warning.

scope:
  in:
    - Checkout overnight rate fetch — add post-fetch comparison against FE constant
    - Mismatch: display BE rate (source of truth) + Sentry.captureMessage with delta
    - Unit test: matching rates → no warning; mismatched → Sentry called + BE rate shown
  out:
    - Changing BE /rates logic
    - Alerts outside Sentry

invariants:
  - BE /rates is always source of truth on mismatch
  - Sentry event must not include raw pricing beyond the delta amount

acceptance:
  - Rate match: no Sentry event, FE shows constant value
  - Rate mismatch: FE shows BE value, Sentry warning with delta
  - Unit tests cover both paths

dep: none
output: checkout overnight rate fetch patched + unit tests
